+        # Boot chain on this board:
+        #   1. SoC ROM loads U-Boot from QSPI NOR flash
+        #   2. U-Boot reads its environment from QSPI NOR ("uboot-env"
+        #      MTD partition).  The env var `bootcmd` selects what to
+        #      load; `vyos_image` selects which installed image dir.
+        #   3. U-Boot reads /boot/vyos.env from eMMC partition 3 to learn
+        #      the active image name (written here, below).
+        #   4. U-Boot loads vmlinuz/initrd/dtb from
+        #      /boot/<image>/  on eMMC and jumps to the kernel.
+        #
+        # Two things therefore have to be configured at install time:
+        #   (a) /boot/vyos.env  on the eMMC root partition  -- always
+        #       writable, this script writes it directly.
+        #   (b) U-Boot env vars in QSPI NOR (`bootcmd`, `vyos_image`,
+        #       `usb_vyos`) -- requires CONFIG_MTD + CONFIG_SPI in the
+        #       running kernel so /dev/mtd2 exists for fw_setenv.
+        #       If absent, the user must set them once from the U-Boot
+        #       prompt; see vyos-ls1046a-build/INSTALL.md.
+        # ------------------------------------------------------------
